data.content:
Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘['tæηglid]
*tính từ
 ■rối, lộn xộn
 ⁃tangled hair
 tóc rối
 ⁃tangled wire
 dây thép rối

Từ điển Đồng nghĩa
tangled
▸ adjective
1tangled hair: KNOTTED, knotty, ravelled, entangled, snarled (up), twisted, matted, tangly, messy; tousled, unkempt, ratty; informal mussed up.
2a tangled bureaucratic mess: CONFUSED, jumbled, mixed up, messy, chaotic, complicated, involved, complex, intricate, knotty, tortuous.
Opposites
simple.

sentences.en: But somehow our feet got all tangled up, knocking us both off balance.

sentences.en: An analyst commented that things have become ‘tangled like bamboo shavings’.

sentences.en: After I brushed my teeth, I worked to straighten out the tangled chaos that was my hair.
sentences.vi: Sau khi chải răng, tôi hì hục chải cho thẳng mớ lộn xộn rối nùi vốn là mái tóc của tôi.
